OL,7,F"I still remember the day when I was
OL,8,Fwatching the news, and it said Kabul
OL,9,Fhad been taken over by the Taliban. I
OL,10,Fwas crying, and telling myself, oh
OL,11,Fwhat will happen to you?
OL,13,F"We fled from our country to here. We
OL,14,Fdidn't lose our identity, I'm still
OL,15,FAfghan and I'm proud to be Afghan, but
OL,16,FI just lost one thing, and it is just
OL,17,Fbeing in the Afghan national team, as
OL,18,FI was before, and it's a really
OL,19,Fdifficult feeling to describe."
